# Generated files — never hand-merge these. They're fully derived from
# tokens.css/tokens.json (and, for dashboard-data, git history) by
# scripts/design-sync.js and scripts/generate-dashboard-data.js; a
# line-based 3-way merge across two branches that each regenerated the
# same file independently produces either a spurious conflict or a
# "successful" merge that's really just whichever side's diff happened to
# apply cleanly — neither is a real answer. `merge=ours` makes git skip
# the merge for these paths entirely and keep the current side, no
# conflict markers, no partial-line-merge risk. That's fine specifically
# because the correct post-merge content isn't "ours" or "theirs" — it's
# whatever `npm run design-sync && npm run dashboard-data` produces
# against the merged tokens, which must be run afterward regardless of
# what this driver picked. See package.json's `prepare` script, which
# registers the `ours` driver locally on `npm install`/`npm ci` — without
# that one-time config, git silently falls back to a normal merge for
# these paths instead of erroring, so this file alone doesn't guarantee
# the behavior; re-run `npm run design-sync`/`npm run dashboard-data`
# after any merge that touches tokens.css/tokens.json regardless.
src/design-docs/*.generated.json merge=ours
src/components/*/*.validation.json merge=ours
